</script>
```

In this example, we have a component that renders a list of items. The items array in the `data` section represents your enumerator. Each item has an `id` and a `label`. The `v-for` directive is used to iterate over the items array and render the list items.

If you need to use the enumerator values in other parts of your component or manipulate them dynamically, you can use a computed property:

