        for i, gpu in enumerate(vram_info):
            ram_usage[f"gpu_{i}_total_vram"] = int(gpu[0]) * 1024 * 1024  # Convert to bytes
            ram_usage[f"gpu_{i}_used_vram"] = int(gpu[1]) * 1024 * 1024  # Convert to bytes
    else:
        # Set all VRAM-related entries to None
        ram_usage["gpu_0_total_vram"] = None
        ram_usage["gpu_0_used_vram"] = None

    return ram_usage
```

In this updated code, I've multiplied the VRAM values by 1024 * 1024 to convert them from megabytes to bytes. Now the `ram_usage` dictionary will contain the VRAM values in bytes for each GPU.

