To connect to a Socket.IO server, you'll typically use a WebSocket client library or a Socket.IO client library, depending on the programming language you're using. Here's an example using JavaScript:

```javascript
// Import the Socket.IO client library
import io from 'socket.io-client';

// Connect to the Socket.IO server
const socket = io('http://localhost:9600');

// Event handler for successful connection
socket.on('connect', () => {
  console.log('Connected to Socket.IO server');
});

